title: Disco Beans
typeOfFood: Vegan-friendly, Lacto, Ovo, Japanese, Fusion, Non-veg
description: Serves meat, veg options available. Primarily a home-cooking Japanese fusion restaurant that makes mostly vegetarian/vegan food along with fish in a few dishes. Vegan such as the disco di fiesta (guacamole, beans, tomato sauce, and corn chips on rice), disco bonanza (pan fried tofu with baked mushroom on toast), and stir-fried sukiyaki udon noodle. The premises is also an art gallery.
